You can compose them via `flatMapCompletable`, for example:

```java
public Single<Book> saveBook(Book book) {
    return exist(book)
           .flatMapCompletable(exists -> exists ? Completable.complete() : bookRepo.save(book))
           .andThen(Single.just(book));
```

It depends on how you structured your save-update workflow.

One possibility is to cache the `saveBook` above; it will make sure the save runs at most once and there will be a value ready after, indicating the save completed.

```java
Single<Book> bookCached = saveBook(book).cache();
bookCached.subscribe(/* trigger the save */);

// later
bookCached
  .flatMap(book -> updateBook(book))
  .subscribe(/* trigger update */)
```

