comments.body:
> This is pretty confusing and looks like not consistent

Please consider that the operators have to work with the specific protocols of the participating reactive types. For example, there is no `onComplete` in `Single` thus a `takeUntil` can't complete a `Single` like it would an `Observable`.

> make takeUntil() call onError(CancellationException)

Nothing is preventing you from getting `onError` called on `terminationSignal`:

```java
CompletableSubject terminationSignal = CompletableSubject.create();

completable.takeUntil(terminationSignal)
    .subscribe(() -> {
        System.out.println("Should not be called");
    }, e -> {
        e.printStackTrace();
    });

terminationSignal.onError(new CancellationException());
```

or, if you have a cold termination signal, compose in the exception:

```java
Completable terminationSignal = ...

completable.takeUntil(
        terminationSignal.andThen(
            Completable.fromAction(() -> { throw new CancellationException(); })
        )
    )
    .subscribe(() -> {
        System.out.println("Should not be called");
    }, e -> {
        e.printStackTrace();
    });
```

