What I'd expect and think is desirable is eviction kicking in after about 60s or so.
But it seems that is as soon as something is executed by the IO scheduler the eviction timer resets and so the pool will never shrink until it is left completely unused for 60 seconds.

Our application pretty much never leaves the IO scheduler unused for such a long time...

