Thanks for using RxJava but before you post an issue, please consider the following points:

  - RxJava Version: 1.2.7

Overview:
I wanted to test the scenario where I use RxJava to poll a service. The expectation is that the service will return a list with transactions, an empty list, or an exception will be thrown. Whenever, a list with transactions is returned they will be published to any subscribe to the relevant Rx subject. From Rx perspective polling and retry will be indefinite by will be throttled and the intent is to use a circuit breaker higher up the call stack to reduce necessary calls when the server is not available. 

In my research all works as expected if you return list data, empty list or throw an exception. However, if one was to return say:

  Observable.error(new RuntimeException());

Then resubscription does not appear to take place.

Here's the pretty much self contain code.  I've made it so that I can simulate having a mix of list items, empty list or exception returning. I can also have a specific set of the above options return. Additionally, I can simulate throwing an exception or returning Observable.error(...).

```java
package com.shapestone.transaction.publisher;

import rx.Observable;
import rx.Observer;
import rx.Subscription;
import rx.subjects.PublishSubject;
import rx.subjects.Subject;

import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;
