I wrote some testcode that causes an `ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException` on almost every run and i do not understand why, how to avoid it or if this is a bug in (rx)java.

The exception is thrown in `ArrayList#add(E e)` by calling `elementData[size++] = e;` where a call of `ensureCapacityInternal(size+1)` should have made sure that the capacity is sufficient. I assume some concurrency-related problem.

What the code was intended to do:  Start a new "WorkerThread" every second that produces Strings at a given rate and collect the resulting items of all those workers (here called "Minions") in one re-playable `Observable<String>`. 
The actual parameters are just set to increase probability of this exception to be thrown.

``` java
